Items.Name: Afcon Contracting & Services Ltd
Items.Description:
Afcon Manufacturing has extensive expertise in the design, production, and installation of electrical and switchgear panels for medium and low voltages. These advanced products for infrastructure and electrical transmission are manufactured at its Beer-Sheva plant, based on exclusive technology in cooperation with leading international companies such as ABB.

Afcon Manufacturing has been in operation since 1945, and today is Israel largest, market-leading manufacturer of type tested electrical panels and switchgear with air or gas insulation for low and medium voltages up to 36KV.

Its advanced products include control panels, primary and secondary electrical distribution panels, starter panels, all switchgears, mobile structures and low voltage panels, per Afcon system up to 6300 ampere, which reinforces the plant position at the forefront of world technology.

Items.Description:
Al Majal Logistics Services (AMLS), is a subsidiary of Al Majal – a leading group of Iraqi companies that offer a wide range of products and services to the most prominent companies operating within the energy sector in Iraq. Founded in 2008, Al Majal is headquartered in Basra with operations in Baghdad and Erbil, and regional offices in Dubai and Amman. Leveraging the strength of its subsidiaries, Al Majal continues to deliver innovative and impactful solutions to clients and partners across Iraq.

The AMLS team is committed to supporting the seamless operations of your business through safe and timely transport, handling and storage of equipment and goods. Our client-centric and cost-effective solutions ensure that your valuable time and resources are directed towards your core business operations.

Items.Name: AlAkhras Co for Electric & Ind. Services
Items.Description:
ALLESCO was established in 1995 as a private electrical and industrial institution that provides consultations needed to the industrial market in Palestine.
This Company is considered to be one of the biggest institutions Palestine that has helped developing the automatic, electromechanical and the technological industry through an organized work that has always provided what is needed such as: high-quality products and machines, a very qualified stuff that is ready to work under any situation in everywhere in and out the West Bank and too many other services from training courses, supporting graduation projects and providing high quality consultations that are up to date with the new revolution of the computer technology world.
The main first office of the Company was established in Nablus City, however and according to the Palestinians’ market demands, the Company has to expand its work through opening new branches in the two biggest West Banks’ cities: Ramallah and Hebron. But the breaking through of the Company was the foundation of the ALLESCO Factory that is located at the Industrial east part of Nablus City.
This Factory is working on building and producing high-quality electronical and industrial panels. It has been considered to be the only factory in Palestine that works on this without using the traditional manual way of collecting the pieces of the panels: welding. The panels are produced through passing too many stages of a huge organized procedure that includes: iron washing, cleaning, painting and other too many stages till the end of the completed high-quality panels that are ready to be used. Right now the company is working on another breaking through that will become soon a very important step in this technological world through producing very high-quality typetested panels. This is being done through a huge cooperation with internationals companies all around the world and will be finished as soon as possible.

Items.Name: ARB Electrical Wholesalers Pty Ltd
Items.Description:
ARB Electrical Wholesalers is one of Southern Africa’s largest black-
empowered electrical wholesalers, playing a pivotal role in providing the essential materials required for the electrification of large scale industrial and parastatal projects.

ARB began in Richards Bay in 1980, and has since grown drastically to become a nationwide, fully equipped Electrical Wholesaler.

In 2007, The ARB group listed on the Main Board of the JSE. This milestone initiative was deemed necessary to accelerate on-going organic growth and enable ARB to further expand both nationally and across the continent, as well as continue its penetration of new high-growth markets.
